B019C043V001	19	43	1	Right me, defend my causeagainst a pitiless people.From the crafty and crooked,O God, deliver me.
B019C043V002	19	43	2	For you are God my protector:why have you cast me off?Why must I walk so sadly,so hard pressed by the foe?
B019C043V003	19	43	3	Send forth your light and your truth,let them be my guides:to your holy hill let them bring me,to the place where you live.
B019C043V004	19	43	4	Then will I go to God’s altar,to God my rejoicing;and with joy on the lyre I will praise you,O God, my God. 
B019C043V005	19	43	5	Why am I downcast?Why this moaning within me?Hope in God;for yet will I praise him,my help, my God.
B019C044V001	19	44	1	O God, we have heard with our ears,our ancestors have told usof the work that you wrought in their day,your wonders in days of old,
B019C044V002	19	44	2	uprooting and crushing the nations,then planting and settling them.For it wasn’t their own sword that won them the land,
B019C044V003	19	44	3	it was not their own arm that brought them the victory.Yours was the hand and the arm,yours was the face that shone on them with favour.
B019C044V004	19	44	4	It was you, my king and my God,that ordained the victories of Jacob. 
B019C044V005	19	44	5	Through you we can thrust back our foes,and by your name tread down our assailants:
B019C044V006	19	44	6	for not in my bow do I trust,nor can my sword win me the victory.
B019C044V007	19	44	7	Our victory comes from you,and confusion to those who hate us.
B019C044V008	19	44	8	In God we boast all the day long,and your name will we praise forever.  (Selah)  
B019C044V009	19	44	9	Yet you have spurned and disgraced us,in not going forth with our armies,
B019C044V010	19	44	10	and in making us flee from the foe,so that those who hated us plundered us.
B019C044V011	19	44	11	You have let us be eaten like sheep,you have scattered us over the world,
B019C044V012	19	44	12	sold your people for a pittance,and getting no gain from their price.
B019C044V013	19	44	13	You have made us the butt of our neighbours,the derision and scorn of all round us.
B019C044V014	19	44	14	O’er the world you have made us a byword,the nations at us shake their heads.
B019C044V015	19	44	15	My disgrace is forever before me,my face is covered with shame,
B019C044V016	19	44	16	at the words of blasphemer and scoffer,at the sight of the foe and the vengeful. 
B019C044V017	19	44	17	All this has come upon us,yet we have not forgotten younor falsely dealt with your covenant.
B019C044V018	19	44	18	Our heart has not turned back,nor our steps declined from your way,
B019C044V019	19	44	19	that you thus should have crushed us down,and covered us over with gloom,in the place where the jackals roam.
B019C044V020	19	44	20	Had we forgotten the name of our God,or stretched out our hands to a god that was strange,
B019C044V021	19	44	21	would God not have searched this out?For he knows the heart and its secrets.
B019C044V022	19	44	22	But in your cause it is we are killed all the day,and counted as sheep for the slaughter. 
B019C044V023	19	44	23	Rouse yourself, why do you sleep Lord?Awake, cast us not off forever.
B019C044V024	19	44	24	Why do you hide your face,forgetting our stress and our misery?
B019C044V025	19	44	25	For we have sunk down to the dust,our bodies cling to the ground.
B019C044V026	19	44	26	Arise, come to our help:for your love’s sake, ransom us.
B019C045V001	19	45	1	My heart is astir with beautiful words:I will sing a song, concerning the king,with tongue like the pen of a ready writer. 
