B019C049V001	19	49	1	Hear this, you peoples all;give ear, all you who live in the world
B019C049V002	19	49	2	people of low degree and high,the rich and the poor together.
B019C049V003	19	49	3	My mouth shall utter wisdom,the thoughts of a seeing heart.
B019C049V004	19	49	4	I incline my ear to a proverb,on the lyre I will open my riddle. 
B019C049V005	19	49	5	Why should I be afraid in the days of misfortune,when circled by wicked and cunning foes,
B019C049V006	19	49	6	who put their trust in their wealth,and boast of their boundless riches? 
B019C049V007	19	49	7	For assuredly no one can ransom themselves,or give to God the price of their life,
B019C049V008	19	49	8	for the ransom of a life is costly,no payment is ever enough,
B019C049V009	19	49	9	to keep them alive for ever and ever,so as never to see the pit at all. 
B019C049V010	19	49	10	But see it they shall. Even wise people die,the fool and the brutish perish alike,and abandon their wealth to others.
B019C049V011	19	49	11	The grave is their everlasting home,the place they shall live in for ever and ever,though after their own names they called whole lands.
B019C049V012	19	49	12	Humans do not sustain their wealth,like the beasts they perish. 
B019C049V013	19	49	13	This is the fate of the confident fool,and the end of those who are pleased with their portion.  (Selah)
B019C049V014	19	49	14	Like sheep they descend to Sheolwith Death for their shepherd;down they go straight to the grave,and their form wastes away in their home below. 
B019C049V015	19	49	15	But God will assuredly ransom my lifefrom the hand of Sheol;for he will receive me.  (Selah)
B019C049V016	19	49	16	So be not afraid when someone grows rich,when the wealth of their house increases.
B019C049V017	19	49	17	Not a shred of it all can they take when they die,wealth cannot follow them down.
B019C049V018	19	49	18	Though they count themselves happy, when they are alive,and win praise from people for faring so well,
B019C049V019	19	49	19	they must join their ancestors,who see the light nevermore.
B019C049V020	19	49	20	Humans do not sustain their wealth,like the beasts they perish.
B019C050V001	19	50	1	The 
B019C050V002	19	50	2	From Zion, perfection of beauty,God’s glory shines forth.
B019C050V003	19	50	3	Our God comes, he cannot keep silence,devouring fire is before him,and furious tempest around him.
B019C050V004	19	50	4	He summons the heavens aboveand the earth to judge his people.
