B019C050V006	19	50	6	that the heavens may declare his justice,for a God of justice is he.  (Selah)  
B019C050V007	19	50	7	“Hear, O my people, and I will speak,and protest to you, O Israel:I am the 
B019C050V008	19	50	8	Not for your sacrifices will I reprove youyour burnt-offerings are ever before me
B019C050V009	19	50	9	Not a bullock will I take from your house,nor he-goats out of your folds;
B019C050V010	19	50	10	for all beasts of the forest are mine,and the kine on a thousand hills.
B019C050V011	19	50	11	I know all the birds of the air,all that moves on the fields is mine.
B019C050V012	19	50	12	Were I hungry, I would not tell you,for the world and its fulness are mine.
B019C050V013	19	50	13	Am I such as to eat bulls’ flesh,or drink the blood of goats?
B019C050V014	19	50	14	Offer to God a thank-offering,pay the Most High your vows.
B019C050V015	19	50	15	Summon me in the day of distress,I will rescue you, so will you honour me.” 
B019C050V016	19	50	16	But to the wicked God says:“What right have you to talk of my statutes,or take my covenant into your mouth
B019C050V017	19	50	17	While you yourself hate correction,and cast my words behind you?
B019C050V018	19	50	18	When you see a thief, you run with them;with adulterers you keep company.
B019C050V019	19	50	19	You let your mouth loose for evil,your tongue contrives deceit.
B019C050V020	19	50	20	You shamefully speak of your kin,and slander your own mother's son.
B019C050V021	19	50	21	And because I kept silence at this,you did take me for one like yourself.But I will convict you and show you plainly. 
B019C050V022	19	50	22	Now you who forget God, mark this,lest I rend you, past hope of deliverance.
B019C050V023	19	50	23	Those who bring a thank-offering honour me;but to those who follow my way,I will show the salvation of God.”
B019C051V001	19	51	1	In your kindness, O God, be gracious to me,in your own great pity blot out my transgressions.
B019C051V002	19	51	2	Wash me clean of my guilt,make me pure of my sin. 
B019C051V003	19	51	3	For well I know my transgressions,my sin is ever before me.
B019C051V004	19	51	4	Against you, only you, have I sinned,and done that which is wrong in your sight:you therefore are just when you speak,and clear when you utter judgment.
B019C051V005	19	51	5	See! In guilt was I brought to the birth,and in sin did my mother conceive me.
B019C051V006	19	51	6	It’s the innermost truth you desire,give me therefore true wisdom of heart. 
B019C051V007	19	51	7	Purge me clean with hyssop,wash me whiter than snow.
B019C051V008	19	51	8	Fill me with joy and gladness,let the bones you have broken rejoice.
B019C051V009	19	51	9	Hide your face from my sins,and blot out my guilt altogether. 
B019C051V010	19	51	10	Create me a clean heart, O God,put a new steadfast spirit within me.
B019C051V011	19	51	11	Cast me not forth from your presence,withdraw not your holy spirit.
B019C051V012	19	51	12	Give me back the joy of your help,with a willing spirit sustain me. 
B019C051V013	19	51	13	I will teach your ways to transgressors,and sinners shall turn to you.
B019C051V014	19	51	14	Save me from blood, O God,and my tongue shall ring out your faithfulness.
B019C051V015	19	51	15	Open my lips, O 
B019C051V016	19	51	16	For in sacrifice you have no pleasure,in gifts of burnt-offering no delight.
B019C051V017	19	51	17	The sacrifice pleasing to Godis a spirit that is broken;a heart that is crushed, O God,you will not despise. 
B019C051V018	19	51	18	Do good in your pleasure to Zion,build the walls of Jerusalem.
B019C051V019	19	51	19	Then will you welcome the due forms of sacrifice,then on your altars shall bullocks be offered.
B019C052V001	19	52	1	Why glory in mischief, man of power?God’s kindness is all the day.
B019C052V002	19	52	2	Engulfing ruin you plot,your tongue like a razor sharpened,you practiser of deceit.
B019C052V003	19	52	3	Evil, not good, you love,and falsehood, not words of truth.  (Selah)
B019C052V004	19	52	4	But you love all words that devour,and a tongue that is given to deceit. 
B019C052V005	19	52	5	But God, on his part, shall destroy you forever,grasp you and pluck you out of your tent,and root you out of the land of the living.  (Selah)
B019C052V006	19	52	6	Smitten with awe at the sight,the righteous shall laugh at you.
B019C052V007	19	52	7	“Look” (they will say) “at the herowho did not make God his stronghold,but trusted in his great wealthand in the strength of his riches.” 
B019C052V008	19	52	8	But I am like a fresh olive-treein the house of God.I trust in the kindness of Godfor ever and evermore.
B019C052V009	19	52	9	I will render you thanks for everfor what you have done.I will tell how good you arein the presence of those who love you.
B019C053V001	19	53	1	Fools say in their heart,“There is no God.”Vile, hateful their life is;not one does good. 
B019C053V002	19	53	2	From heaven God looks outon humans, to seeif any are wise,and care for God. 
B019C053V003	19	53	3	But all have turned bad,the taint is on all;not one does good,no, not one. 
B019C053V004	19	53	4	Have they learned their lesson,those workers of evil?Who ate up my people,eating, devouring,never calling to the 
B019C053V005	19	53	5	Sore afraid will they be,where no fear was;when God scatters the bonesof the godless people.They will be put to shame,when God rejects them. 
B019C053V006	19	53	6	If only help from Zionwould come for Israel!When God brings his peoplea change of fortune,how glad will be Jacob,and Israel how joyful!
B019C054V001	19	54	1	Save me, O God, by your name,by your power secure for me justice.
B019C054V002	19	54	2	Listen, O God, to my prayer,give ear to the words of my mouth.
B019C054V003	19	54	3	For proud men have risen against me,and terrible men seek my life,men who do not set God before them.  (Selah)  
B019C054V004	19	54	4	But see! God is my helper,the 
B019C054V005	19	54	5	Let their evil fall back on my foes:cut them off in your faithfulness, 
B019C054V006	19	54	6	Then will I bring you glad sacrifice,praising your gracious name;
B019C054V007	19	54	7	for from all distress you have saved me,and feasted my eyes on my foes.
B019C055V001	19	55	1	Listen, God, to my prayer.Don’t hide yourself from my pleading.
B019C055V002	19	55	2	Hear me, and answer;for bitter is my lament.
B019C055V003	19	55	3	I am wild with the noise of the foe,with the clamour of the ungodly;for they hurl disaster upon me,and attack me with fury.
B019C055V004	19	55	4	My heart shudders within me,terrors of deaths press on me,
B019C055V005	19	55	5	fear and trembling attack me,and horror wraps me round.
B019C055V006	19	55	6	O for the wings of a dove:I would fly away and rest.
B019C055V007	19	55	7	I would wander far away,find refuge in the wilderness.  (Selah)
B019C055V008	19	55	8	I would find myself a shelterfrom raging wind and tempest. 
B019C055V009	19	55	9	Confuse them, 
B019C055V010	19	55	10	By day and by night they make their roundson the city walls,while within is crime and trouble,
B019C055V011	19	55	11	within is ruin.Her market-place is never freeof deceit and tyranny. 
B019C055V012	19	55	12	The taunts were not those of a foethat I could have borne;the disdain was not that of an enemyI could have shunned them:
B019C055V013	19	55	13	but it was you, my equal,my dear and familiar friend.
B019C055V014	19	55	14	We used to be so close,together we walked in God’s house with the crowd.
B019C055V015	19	55	15	May death suddenly take them,may they go down to Sheol alive,for evil lives in their homes and their hearts. 
B019C055V016	19	55	16	But I will call on God,the 
B019C055V017	19	55	17	Evening and morning and noonI lament and moan.He will hear my voice;
B019C055V018	19	55	18	though I am attacked by manyhe will rescue me,unharmed from the war.
B019C055V019	19	55	19	God, who sits on his ancient thronewill hear and will humble them,for they never change,they never fear God.  (Selah)  
B019C055V020	19	55	20	My friend turned against me,betrayed his word.
B019C055V021	19	55	21	His mouth was smoother than butter,but war filled his heart.His words were softer than oil,but sharper than swords.
B019C055V022	19	55	22	Cast your burden on the 
B019C055V023	19	55	23	But you, God, will hurl them downto the deepest pit.Bloody and treacherous peoplewill not live out half their days;but I will trust you.
B019C056V001	19	56	1	O God, be gracious to me,for people trample upon me,all the day righting and pressing me.
B019C056V002	19	56	2	All the day enemies trample me;many there bewho contend with me bitterly.
B019C056V003	19	56	3	In the day of my terrorI trust in you.
B019C056V004	19	56	4	In God I maintain my cause,in God I fearlessly trust.What can flesh do to me? 
B019C056V005	19	56	5	They torture me all the day,they ceaselessly plan to hurt me,
B019C056V006	19	56	6	banded together in secret,watching my every step,as those who hope for my death.
B019C056V007	19	56	7	Pay them out for their sin, O God,hurl down the strong in your anger.
B019C056V008	19	56	8	You yourself count my wanderings.Put in your bottle my tearsare they not in your book?
B019C056V009	19	56	9	Then shall my foes be turned backin the day that I call.Of this I am sure,because God is for me.
B019C056V010	19	56	10	In God I maintain my cause,in the 
B019C056V011	19	56	11	In God I fearlessly trust,what can people do to me? 
B019C056V012	19	56	12	Your vows are upon me, O God,I will render thank-offerings to you;
B019C056V013	19	56	13	because you have saved me from death,my feet from stumbling,to the end that I walk before Godin the light of the living.
B019C057V001	19	57	1	Be gracious, O God, be gracious to me,for in you I take shelter.In your sheltering wings I take refuge,till ruin be over past.
B019C057V002	19	57	2	I cry to the Most High God,to the God who accomplishes for me.
B019C057V003	19	57	3	He will send me his succour from heaven,he will thrust away those who would trample me.  (Selah)
B019C057V004	19	57	4	In the midst of lions I lie,who devour human prey.Their teeth are spears and arrows,and their tongue is a sharpened sword.
B019C057V005	19	57	5	Be exalted, God, o’er the heavens,and your glory o’er all the earth. 
B019C057V006	19	57	6	They set a net for my feet,but in it was their own foot caught.Before me they dug a pit,but they fell into it themselves.  (Selah)  
B019C057V007	19	57	7	My heart is steadfast, O God,my heart is steadfast.I would sing, I would make music;
B019C057V008	19	57	8	awake, my soul.Awake, harp and lyre;I would wake the dawn.
B019C057V009	19	57	9	I would praise you among the peoples, O 
B019C057V010	19	57	10	for great to heaven is your love,and your faithfulness to the clouds.
B019C057V011	19	57	11	Be exalted, God, o’er the heavens,and your glory o’er all the earth.
B019C058V001	19	58	1	Do you speak what is right, you gods?With equity judge you your people?
B019C058V002	19	58	2	In the land you practise iniquity --- all of you;violence do you dispense with your hands.
B019C058V003	19	58	3	The wicked go astray from the wombliars take the wrong path from their birth.
B019C058V004	19	58	4	Venom have they like the venom of snakes,they are like the deaf adder that stops her ears,
B019C058V005	19	58	5	and refuses to listen to the voice of the charmer,or binder of spells, no matter how cunning. 
B019C058V006	19	58	6	O God, break to pieces the teeth in their mouth,tear out the great teeth of the young lions, 
B019C058V007	19	58	7	May they melt away like running water!Like tender grass, cut down may they be!
B019C058V008	19	58	8	Like the snail that dissolves on its crawling path,like the birth untimely which sees not the sunlight.
B019C058V009	19	58	9	Faster than a thorn-fire heats your pots,he will come with his tempest and sweep them away.
B019C058V010	19	58	10	The sight of such vengeance will gladden the righteous;their feet they will wash in the blood of the wicked.
B019C058V011	19	58	11	People will say, “Yes, the just are rewarded:yes, on the earth is a God who is judge.”
B019C059V001	19	59	1	Save me, O God, from my enemies;secure me from my assailants.
B019C059V002	19	59	2	Save me from those who do wrong,save me from the bloodthisty.
