B019C059V004	19	59	4	they run and make ready. Awake!Come forth to meet me, and see!
B019C059V005	19	59	5	You, O 
B019C059V006	19	59	6	At evening they come,and, howling like dogs,make their round in the city.
B019C059V007	19	59	7	Look at their venomous mouths,tongues like swords,they think no onehears them.
B019C059V008	19	59	8	But you, 
B019C059V009	19	59	9	My strength, I will sing to you,for God is my sure retreat.
B019C059V010	19	59	10	My God with his love will meet me,and feast my eyes on my foes. 
B019C059V011	19	59	11	Slay them not, lest my people forget,let your hosts keep them roaming and wandering.
B019C059V012	19	59	12	In their sinful speech snare them, O 
B019C059V013	19	59	13	In your wrath make a clean end of them,that people, to the ends of the earth,may know that God rules in Jacob.  (Selah)  
B019C059V014	19	59	14	At evening they come,and, howling like dogs,make their round in the city.
B019C059V015	19	59	15	They roam about for a feast,and snarl, if they get not their fill.
B019C059V016	19	59	16	But I will sing of your might;I will ring out your love in the morning.For to me you have been a sure refuge,a retreat in the day of my trouble.
B019C059V017	19	59	17	My strength, I will sing praise to you,for God is my sure retreat,my faithful God.
B019C060V001	19	60	1	O God, you have spurned and broken us,routing us in your wrath --- restore us!
B019C060V002	19	60	2	You have shaken the land and cleft it;heal its tottering breaches.
B019C060V003	19	60	3	You have made your people drink hardship,and given us wine of reeling. 
B019C060V004	19	60	4	You have given those who fear you a banner,a rallying-place from the bow,  (Selah)
B019C060V005	19	60	5	for the rescue of your beloved.Save by your right hand and answer us. 
B019C060V006	19	60	6	God did solemnly swear:“As victor will I divide Shechem,and mete out the valley of Succoth.
B019C060V007	19	60	7	Mine is Gilead, mine is Manasseh,Ephraim is the defence of my head,Judah my sceptre of rule,
B019C060V008	19	60	8	Moab the pot that I wash in,Edom — I cast my shoe over it,I shout o’er Philistia in triumph.” 
B019C060V009	19	60	9	O to be brought to the fortified city!O to be led into Edom!
B019C060V010	19	60	10	Have you not spurned us, O God?You do not march forth with our armies.
B019C060V011	19	60	11	Grant us help from the foe,for human help is worthless.
B019C060V012	19	60	12	With God we shall yet do bravely:he himself will tread down our foes.
B019C061V001	19	61	1	Hear my cry, O God,be attentive to my prayer.
B019C061V002	19	61	2	From the ends of the earth I callunto you, when my heart is faint:lead me to the rockthat is high above me.
B019C061V003	19	61	3	For you are a refuge to me,a strong tower in face of the foe. 
B019C061V004	19	61	4	O to be guest in your tent forever,hiding beneath your sheltering wings!  (Selah)
B019C061V005	19	61	5	For you, O God, do hear my vows,and grant the desires of those who fear you.
B019C061V006	19	61	6	Add many days to the life of the king;may his years endure throughout all generations.
B019C061V007	19	61	7	In the presence of God be he throned forever;may kindness and faithfulness watch over him.
B019C061V008	19	61	8	And I will sing praise to your name forever,paying my vows day after day.
B019C062V001	19	62	1	I wait alone in silence for God;From him comes my help.
B019C062V002	19	62	2	Yes, he is my rock, my help, my retreat,I shall not be shaken too sorely.
B019C062V003	19	62	3	How long will you, all of you, batter a man,as one might a leaning wall?
