B019C062V012	19	62	12	and to you, too, O 
B019C063V001	19	63	1	O God, my God, you, you do I seek:my heart thirsts for you,my body faints for youin a parched and waterless land. 
B019C063V002	19	63	2	As I in the temple have seen you,beholding your power and your glory,
B019C063V003	19	63	3	for better than life is your kindness:my lips shall utter your praise. 
B019C063V004	19	63	4	So, while I live, I will bless you,and lift up my hands in your name.
B019C063V005	19	63	5	As with marrow and fat am I feasted;with joyful lips I will praise you. 
B019C063V006	19	63	6	I call you to mind on my bed,and muse on you in the night watches;
B019C063V007	19	63	7	for you have been my help,I joyfully sing in the shadow of your wings.
B019C063V008	19	63	8	I cling close after you,your right hand holds me up. 
B019C063V009	19	63	9	But those who seek after my lifeshall go down to the depths of the earth,
B019C063V010	19	63	10	given o’er to the power of the sword,or as prey for jackals to devour. 
B019C063V011	19	63	11	But the king shall rejoice in God:all who own his allegiance will glory.For the mouth of the false shall be stopped.
B019C064V001	19	64	1	Hear, O my God, the voice of my lament:guard my life from the foe who affrights me.
B019C064V002	19	64	2	Hide me from villains who secretly plot,from the blustering throng of the workers of evil,
B019C064V003	19	64	3	who have sharpened their tongue like a sword,and aimed bitter words like arrows,
B019C064V004	19	64	4	which from ambush they launch at the blameless,shooting swiftly and unafraid. 
