B019C064V006	19	64	6	They think out their crimes full cunninglyhidden deep in their crafty hearts. 
B019C064V007	19	64	7	But God with his arrow will shoot them,swiftly shall they be smitten.
B019C064V008	19	64	8	For their tongue he will bring them to ruin,all will shudder with horror at the sight of them. 
B019C064V009	19	64	9	Then every person, touched to awe,as they ponder what God has wrought,will tell the tale of his deeds.
