B019C065V001	19	65	1	It is seemly to praise you, O God, in Zion,and to you shall the vow be performed in Jerusalem.
B019C065V002	19	65	2	O you who hear prayer,unto you shall all flesh come.
B019C065V003	19	65	3	Our sins are too mighty for us,our transgressions you only can cover them.
B019C065V004	19	65	4	Happy the person whom you chooseto live beside you in your courts.O may we be filled with the joysof your house, of your holy temple. 
B019C065V005	19	65	5	In dread deeds you loyally answer us,O God of our salvation,whom all ends of the earth put their trust in,and islands far away.
B019C065V006	19	65	6	By your strength you establish the hills,you are armed with might;
B019C065V007	19	65	7	you still the roaring of seas,and the turmoil of nations,
B019C065V008	19	65	8	so that those who live at earth’s boundsare awed at your signs:the lands of the sunrise and sunsetyou make to ring with joy. 
B019C065V009	19	65	9	You visit and water the earth;you greatly enrich herwith the river of God, which is full of water.You prepare the corn thereof,
B019C065V010	19	65	10	watering her furrows,settling her ridges;you make her soft with showers,and bless what grows thereon.
B019C065V011	19	65	11	You crown the year with your goodness,your chariot-tracks drip with fatness.
B019C065V012	19	65	12	The desert pastures are lush,the hills greened with joy.
B019C065V013	19	65	13	The meadows are clothed with flocks,the valleys are covered with corn;they shout to each other and sing.
B019C066V001	19	66	1	Shout to God, all the earth,
B019C066V002	19	66	2	sing praise to his glorious name,sing his glorious praise.
