B019C078V018	19	78	18	They wilfully challenged God,demanding the food that they longed for.
B019C078V019	19	78	19	“Is God able,“ such was their challenge,“to spread in the desert a table?
B019C078V020	19	78	20	From the rock that he struck there gushed water,and torrents that overflowed;but can he also give bread,or provide his people with meat?” 
B019C078V021	19	78	21	When the 
B019C078V022	19	78	22	For they put no trust in God,no confidence in his help.
B019C078V023	19	78	23	So he summoned the clouds above;and, opening the doors of heaven,
B019C078V024	19	78	24	he rained manna upon them for food,and grain of heaven he gave them.
B019C078V025	19	78	25	Everyone ate the bread of angels;he sent them food to the full. 
