B019C109V001	19	109	1	O God whom I praise, keep not silence;for their wicked mouths they have opened against me,they speak to me with tongues that are false,
B019C109V003	19	109	3	they beset me with words of hatred,and fight without cause against me.
B019C109V004	19	109	4	My love they requite with hostility,while for them I lift up my prayer.
B019C109V005	19	109	5	Evil for good they reward me,and hatred for my love. 
B019C109V006	19	109	6	“Set over him one who is godless,” they say,“an opponent at his right hand.
B019C109V007	19	109	7	From his trial let him come forth guilty,may his prayer be counted as sin.
B019C109V008	19	109	8	Grant that his days may be few,that his office be seized by another.
B019C109V009	19	109	9	Grant that his children be fatherless,and that his wife be a widow.
B019C109V010	19	109	10	Up and down may his children go begging,expelled from their desolate home.
B019C109V011	19	109	11	May all that he owns be seized by the creditormay strangers plunder the fruits of his toil. 
B019C109V012	19	109	12	May none extend to him kindness,or pity his fatherless children.
