B040C001V001	40	1	1	A genealogy of Jesus Christ, a descendant of David and Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham was the father of Isaac, Isaac of Jacob, Jacob of Judah and his brothers,
B040C001V003	40	1	3	Judah of Perez and Zerah, whose mother was Tamar, Perez of Hezron, Hezron of Ram,
B040C001V004	40	1	4	Ram of Amminadab, Amminadab of Nashon, Nashon of Salmon,
B040C001V005	40	1	5	Salmon of Boaz, whose mother was Rahab, Boaz of Obed, whose mother was Ruth, Obed of Jesse,
B040C001V006	40	1	6	Jesse of David the King. David was the father of Solomon, whose mother was Uriah’s widow,
B040C001V007	40	1	7	Solomon of Rehoboam, Rehoboam of Abijah, Abijah of Asa,
B040C001V008	40	1	8	Asa of Jehoshaphat, Jehoshaphat of Jehoram, Jehoram of Uzziah,
B040C001V009	40	1	9	Uzziah of Jotham, Jotham of Ahaz, Ahaz of Hezekiah,
B040C001V010	40	1	10	Hezekiah of Manasseh, Manasseh of Ammon, Ammon of Josiah,
B040C001V011	40	1	11	Josiah of Jeconiah and his brothers, at the time of the Exile to Babylon.
B040C001V012	40	1	12	After the Exile to Babylon — Jeconiah was the father of Shealtiel, Shealtiel of Zerubbabel,
B040C001V013	40	1	13	Zerubbabel of Abiud, Abiud of Eliakim, Eliakim of Azor,
B040C001V014	40	1	14	Azor of Zadok, Zadok of Achim, Achim of Eliud,
B040C001V015	40	1	15	Eliud of Eleazar, Eleazar of Matthan, Matthan of Jacob,
B040C001V016	40	1	16	Jacob of Joseph, the husband of Mary, who was the mother of Jesus, who is called ‘Christ’.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	So the whole number of generations from Abraham to David is fourteen; from David to the Exile to Babylon fourteen; and from the Exile to Babylon to the Christ fourteen.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	This is how Jesus Christ was born:  His mother Mary was engaged to Joseph, but, before the marriage took place, she found herself to be pregnant by the power of the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	Her husband, Joseph, was a religious man and, since he did not want to disgrace her publicly, he resolved to put an end to their engagement privately.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	He had been thinking this over, when an angel of the Lord appeared to him in a dream.  “Joseph, son of David,” the angel said, “do not be afraid to take Mary for your wife, for her child has been conceived by the power of the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	She will give birth to a son; name him Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins.”  
B040C001V022	40	1	22	All this happened in fulfilment of these words of the Lord in the prophet, where he says —
B040C001V023	40	1	23	‘The virgin will conceive and will give birth to a son, and they will give him the name Immanuel’  — a word which means ‘God is with us.’
B040C001V024	40	1	24	When Joseph woke up, he did as the angel of the Lord had directed him.
B040C001V025	40	1	25	He made Mary his wife, but they did not sleep together until after the birth of her son; and to this son he gave the name Jesus.  
B040C002V001	40	2	1	After the birth of Jesus at Bethlehem in Judea, in the reign of King Herod, some astrologers from the East arrived in Jerusalem, asking:
B040C002V002	40	2	2	“Where is the newborn king of the Jews? For we saw his star in the east, and have come to worship him.”
B040C002V003	40	2	3	When King Herod heard of this, he was much troubled, and so, too, was all Jerusalem.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	He called together all the chief priests and teachers of the law in the nation, and questioned them as to where the Christ was to be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	“At Bethlehem in Judea,” was their answer; “for it is said in the prophet —
B040C002V006	40	2	6	‘And you, Bethlehem in Judah’s land,are in no way least among the chief cities of Judah;for out of you will come a ruler —who will shepherd my people Israel.’” 
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod secretly sent for the astrologers, and found out from them the date of the appearance of the star;
B040C002V008	40	2	8	and, sending them to Bethlehem, he said: “Go and make careful inquiries about the child, and, as soon as you have found him, bring me word so that I, too, can go and worship him.”
B040C002V009	40	2	9	The astrologers heard what the king had to say, and then continued their journey. The star which they had seen in the east led them on, until it reached, and stood over, the place where the child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	At the sight of the star they were filled with joy.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	Entering the house, they saw the child with his mother, Mary, and fell at his feet and worshipped him. Then they opened their treasure chests, and offered to the child presents of gold, frankincense, and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	But afterwards, having been warned in a dream not to go back to Herod, they returned to their own country by another road.  
B040C002V013	40	2	13	After they had left, an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream, and said:  “Get up, take the child and his mother, and seek refuge in Egypt; and stay there until I tell you to return, for Herod is about to search for the child, to put him to death.”
B040C002V014	40	2	14	Joseph woke up, and taking the child and his mother by night, went into Egypt,
B040C002V015	40	2	15	and there he stayed until Herod’s death; in fulfilment of these words of the Lord in the prophet, where he says —  ‘Out of Egypt I called my Son.’ 
B040C002V016	40	2	16	When Herod found out that the astrologers had tricked him, he flew into a rage. He sent and put to death all the boys in Bethlehem and the whole of that neighbourhood, who were two years old or under, guided by the date which he had learned from the astrologers.
B040C002V017	40	2	17	Then were fulfilled these words spoken in the prophet Jeremiah, where he says —
B040C002V018	40	2	18	‘A voice was heard in Ramah,weeping and mourning loudly;Rachel, weeping for her children,refusing all comfort for they were dead.’ 
B040C002V019	40	2	19	But, on the death of Herod, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt, and said:
B040C002V020	40	2	20	“Get up, take the child and his mother, and go into the Land of Israel, for those who sought to take the child’s life are dead.”
B040C002V021	40	2	21	He woke up, and taking the child and his mother, went into the Land of Israel.
B040C002V022	40	2	22	But, hearing that Archelaus had succeeded his father Herod as king of Judea, he was afraid to go back there; and having been warned in a dream, he went into the part of the country called Galilee.
B040C002V023	40	2	23	There he settled in the town of Nazareth, in fulfilment of these words in the prophets — ‘He will be called a Nazarene.’  
B040C003V001	40	3	1	About that time John the Baptist first appeared, proclaiming in the wilderness of Judea:
B040C003V002	40	3	2	“Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.”
B040C003V003	40	3	3	John was the one who was spoken of in the prophet Isaiah, where he says —  ‘The voice of one crying aloud in the wilderness:“Make ready the way of the Lord,make his paths straight.”’
B040C003V004	40	3	4	John’s clothes were made of camels’ hair, with a leather strap round his waist, and his food was locusts and wild honey.
B040C003V005	40	3	5	At that time Jerusalem, and all Judea, as well as the whole district of the Jordan, went out to him
B040C003V006	40	3	6	and were baptized by him in the Jordan River, confessing their sins.  
B040C003V007	40	3	7	But when John saw many of the Pharisees and Sadducees coming to receive his baptism, he said to them:  “You children of snakes! Who has prompted you to seek refuge from the coming judgment?
B040C003V008	40	3	8	Let your life, then, prove your repentance;
B040C003V009	40	3	9	and do not think that you can say among yourselves ‘Abraham is our ancestor,’ for I tell you that out of these stones God is able to raise descendants for Abraham!
B040C003V010	40	3	10	Already the axe is lying at the root of the trees. Therefore every tree that fails to bear good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.
B040C003V011	40	3	11	I, indeed, baptize you with water to teach repentance; but he who is coming after me is more powerful than I, and I am not fit even to carry his sandals. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.
B040C003V012	40	3	12	His winnowing-fan is in his hand, and he will clear his threshing-floor, and store his grain in the barn, but the chaff he will burn with a fire that cannot be put out.”  
B040C003V013	40	3	13	Then Jesus came from Galilee to the Jordan, to John, to be baptized by him.
B040C003V014	40	3	14	But John tried to prevent him. 
B040C003V015	40	3	15	Jesus answered, So John agreed.  
B040C003V016	40	3	16	After the baptism of Jesus, and just as he came up from the water, the heavens opened, and he saw the Spirit of God coming down like a dove and resting on him,
B040C003V017	40	3	17	and from the heavens there came a voice which said: “This is my dearly loved son, who brings me great joy.”  
