B041C015V003	41	15	3	Then the chief priests brought a number of charges against him.
B041C015V004	41	15	4	So Pilate questioned Jesus again. “Have you no reply to make?” he asked. “Listen, how many charges they are bringing against you.”
B041C015V005	41	15	5	But Jesus still made no reply whatever; at which Pilate was astonished.
B041C015V006	41	15	6	Now, at the feast, Pilate used to grant the people the release of any one prisoner whom they might ask for.
B041C015V007	41	15	7	A man called Barabbas was in prison, with the rioters who had committed murder during a riot.
B041C015V008	41	15	8	So, when the crowd went up and began to ask Pilate to follow his usual custom,
B041C015V009	41	15	9	he answered: “Do you want me to release the ‘king of the Jews’ for you?”
B041C015V010	41	15	10	For he was aware that it was out of jealousy that the chief priests had given Jesus up to him.
B041C015V011	41	15	11	But the chief priests incited the crowd to get Barabbas released instead.
B041C015V012	41	15	12	Pilate, however, spoke to them again: “What should I do then with the man whom you call the ‘king of the Jews’?”
B041C015V013	41	15	13	Again they shouted: “Crucify him!”  
B041C015V014	41	15	14	“Why, what harm has he done?” Pilate kept saying to them. But they shouted furiously: “Crucify him!”
B041C015V015	41	15	15	And Pilate, wishing to satisfy the crowd, released Barabbas to them, and, after scourging Jesus, gave him up to be crucified.  
B041C015V016	41	15	16	The soldiers then took Jesus away into the courtyard — that is the Government house — and they called the whole garrison together.
B041C015V017	41	15	17	They dressed him in a purple robe, and, having twisted a crown of thorns, put it on him,
B041C015V018	41	15	18	and then began to salute him. “Long life to you, king of the Jews!” they said.
B041C015V019	41	15	19	And they kept striking him on the head with a rod, spitting at him, and bowing to the ground before him — going down on their knees;
B041C015V020	41	15	20	and, when they had left off mocking him, they took off the purple robe, and put his own clothes on him.  
B041C015V021	41	15	21	They led Jesus out to crucify him; and they compelled a passer-by, Simon from Cyrene, who was on his way in from the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to go with them to carry his cross.
