B042C001V001	42	1	1	To his Excellency, Theophilus.  Many attempts have been already made to draw up an because of those events which have reached their conclusion among us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	just as they were reported to us by those who from the beginning were eye-witnesses, and afterwards became bearers of the message.
B042C001V003	42	1	3	And, therefore, I also, since I have investigated all these events with great care from their very beginning, have resolved to write a connected history of them for you,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	in order that you may be able to satisfy yourself of the accuracy of the story which you have heard from the lips of others.  
B042C001V005	42	1	5	In the reign of Herod, king of Judea, there was a priest named Zechariah, who belonged to the division called after Abijah. His wife, whose name was Elizabeth, was also a descendant of Aaron.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	They were both righteous people, who lived blameless lives, guiding their steps by all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	But they had no child, Elizabeth being barren; and both of them were advanced in years.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	One day, when Zechariah was officiating as priest before God, during the turn of his division,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	it fell to him by lot, in accordance with the practice among the priests, to go into the Temple of the Lord and burn incense;
B042C001V010	42	1	10	and, as it was the Hour of Incense, the people were all praying outside.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	And an angel of the Lord appeared to him, standing on the right of the Altar of Incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	Zechariah was startled at the sight and was awe-struck.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said to him: “Do not be afraid, Zechariah; your prayer has been heard, and your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son, whom you will call by the name John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	He will be to you a joy and a delight; and many will rejoice over his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he will be great in the sight of the Lord; he will not drink any wine or strong drink, and he will be filled with the Holy Spirit from the very hour of his birth,
B042C001V016	42	1	16	and will reconcile many of the Israelites to the Lord their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	He will go before him in the spirit and with the power of Elijah, ‘to reconcile fathers to their children’ and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous, and so make ready for the Lord a people prepared for him.”  
B042C001V018	42	1	18	“How can I be sure of this?” Zechariah asked the angel. “For I am an old man and my wife is advanced in years.”  
B042C001V019	42	1	19	“I am Gabriel,” the angel answered, “who stand in the presence of God, and I have been sent to speak to you and to bring you this good news.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	And now you will be silent and unable to speak until the day when this takes place, because you did not believe what I said, though my words will be fulfilled in due course.”  
B042C001V021	42	1	21	Meanwhile the people were watching for Zechariah, wondering at his remaining so long in the Temple.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	When he came out, he was unable to speak to them, and they perceived that he had seen a vision there. But Zechariah kept making signs to them, and remained dumb.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	And, as soon as his term of service was finished, he returned home.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	After this his wife, Elizabeth, became pregnant and lived in seclusion for five months.
B042C001V025	42	1	25	“The Lord has done this for me,” she said, “he has shown me kindness and taken away the public disgrace of childlessness under which I have been living.”  
B042C001V026	42	1	26	Six months later the angel Gabriel was sent from God to a town in Galilee called Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	to a maiden there who was engaged to a man named Joseph, a descendant of David. Her name was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	Gabriel came into her presence and greeted her, saying: “You have been shown great favour - the Lord is with you..”
B042C001V029	42	1	29	Mary was much disturbed at his words, and was wondering to herself what such a greeting could mean,
B042C001V030	42	1	30	when the angel spoke again: “Do not be afraid, Mary, for you have found favour with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	And now, you will conceive and give birth to a son, and you will give him the name Jesus.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	The child will be great and will be called ‘Son of the Most High,’ and the Lord God will give him the throne of his ancestor David,
B042C001V033	42	1	33	and he will reign over the descendants of Jacob for ever; And to his kingdom there will be no end.”  
B042C001V034	42	1	34	“How can this be?” Mary asked the angel. “For I have no husband.”  
B042C001V035	42	1	35	“The Holy Spirit will descend on you,” answered the angel, “and the Power of the Most High will overshadow you; and therefore the child will be called ‘holy,’ and ‘Son of God.’
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And Elizabeth, your cousin, is herself also expecting a son in her old age; and it is now the sixth month with her, though she is called barren;
B042C001V037	42	1	37	for no promise from God will fail to be fulfilled.”  
B042C001V038	42	1	38	“I am the servant of the Lord,” exclaimed Mary; “let it be with me as you have said.” Then the angel left her.  
B042C001V039	42	1	39	Soon after this Mary set out, and made her way quickly into the hill-country, to a town in Judah;
B042C001V040	42	1	40	and there she went into Zechariah’s house and greeted Elizabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	When Elizabeth heard Mary’s greeting, the child moved within her, and Elizabeth herself was filled with the Holy Spirit,
B042C001V042	42	1	42	and cried aloud: “Blessed are you among women, and blessed is your unborn child!
B042C001V043	42	1	43	But how have I this honour, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For, as soon as your greeting reached my ears, the child moved within me with delight!
B042C001V045	42	1	45	Happy indeed is she who believed that the promise which she received from the Lord would be fulfilled.”  
B042C001V046	42	1	46	And Mary said:  “My soul exalts the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	my spirit delights in God my Saviour;
B042C001V048	42	1	48	for he has remembered his humble servant girl;And from this hour all ages will count me happy!
B042C001V049	42	1	49	Great things has the Almighty done for me;And holy is his name.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	From age to age his mercy restsOn those who honour him.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	Mighty are the deeds of his arm;He scatters the proud with their own devices,
B042C001V052	42	1	52	he casts down princes from their thrones,and the humble he uplifts,
B042C001V053	42	1	53	the hungry he loads with gifts,and the rich he sends empty away.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He has stretched out his hand to his servant Israel,Ever mindful of his mercy
B042C001V055	42	1	55	(As he promised to our forefathers)For Abraham and his race for ever.”
B042C001V056	42	1	56	Mary stayed with Elizabeth about three months, and then returned to her home.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	When Elizabeth’s time came, she gave birth to a son;
B042C001V058	42	1	58	and her neighbours and relations, hearing of the great goodness of the Lord to her, came to share her joy.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	A week later they met to circumcise the child, and were about to call him ‘Zechariah’ after his father,
B042C001V060	42	1	60	when his mother spoke up: “No, he is to be called John.”  
B042C001V061	42	1	61	“You have no relation of that name!” they exclaimed;
B042C001V062	42	1	62	and they made signs to the child’s father, to find out what he wished the child to be called.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	Asking for a writing-tablet, he wrote the words — ‘His name is John.’ Everyone was surprised;
B042C001V064	42	1	64	and immediately Zechariah recovered his voice and the use of his tongue, and began to bless God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	All their neighbours were awe-struck at this; and throughout the hill-country of Judea the whole story was much talked about;
B042C001V066	42	1	66	and all who heard it kept it in mind, asking one another — “What can this child be destined to become?” For the Power of the Lord was with him.  
B042C001V067	42	1	67	Then his father Zechariah was filled with the Holy Spirit, and, speaking under inspiration, said:
B042C001V068	42	1	68	“Blessed is the Lord, the God of Israel,Who has visited his people and wrought their deliverance,
B042C001V069	42	1	69	and has raised up for us the Strength of our salvationIn the house of his servant David —
B042C001V070	42	1	70	As he promised by the lips of his holy prophets of old —
B042C001V071	42	1	71	salvation from our enemies and from the hands of all who hate us,
B042C001V072	42	1	72	showing mercy to our forefathers,And mindful of his sacred covenant.
B042C001V073	42	1	73	This was the oath which he swore to our forefather Abraham —
B042C001V074	42	1	74	That we should be rescued from the hands of our enemies,
B042C001V075	42	1	75	and should serve him without fear in holiness and righteousness,In his presence all our days.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And you, child, will be called prophet of the Most High,For you will go before the Lord to make ready his way,
B042C001V077	42	1	77	to give his people the knowledge of salvationIn the forgiveness of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	through the tender mercy of our God,Whereby the Dawn will break on us from heaven,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	to give light to those who live in darkness and the shadow of death,And guide our feet into the way of peace.”
B042C001V080	42	1	80	The child grew and became strong in spirit; and he lived in the Wilds until the time came for his appearance before Israel.  
B042C002V001	42	2	1	About that time an edict was issued by the Emperor Augustus that a census should be taken of the whole Empire.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	(This was the first census taken while Quirinius was Governor of Syria).
B042C002V003	42	2	3	And everyone went to his own town to be registered.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	Among others Joseph went up from the town of Nazareth in Galilee to Bethlehem, the town of David, in Judea — because he belonged to the family and house of David —
B042C002V005	42	2	5	To be registered with Mary, his engaged wife, who was about to become a mother.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	While they were there her time came,
B042C002V007	42	2	7	and she gave birth to her first child, a son. And because there was no room for them in the inn, she swathed him round and laid him in a manger.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	In that same country-side were shepherds out in the open fields, watching their flocks that night,
B042C002V009	42	2	9	when an angel of the Lord suddenly stood by them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them; and they were seized with fear.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	“Have no fear,” the angel said. “For I bring you good news of a great joy in store for all the nation.
B042C002V011	42	2	11	This day there has been born to you, in the town of David, a Saviour, who is Christ and Lord.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And this will be the sign for you. You will find the infant swathed, and lying in a manger.”
B042C002V013	42	2	13	Then suddenly there appeared with the angel a multitude of the heavenly Host, praising God, and singing —
B042C002V014	42	2	14	“glory to God on high,And on earth peace among those in whom he finds pleasure.”
B042C002V015	42	2	15	Now, when the angels had left them and gone back to heaven, the shepherds said to one another: “Let us go at once to Bethlehem, and see this thing that has happened, of which the Lord has told us.”
B042C002V016	42	2	16	So they went quickly, and found Mary and Joseph, and the infant lying in a manger;
B042C002V017	42	2	17	and, when they saw it, they told of all that had been said to them about this child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	All who heard the shepherds were astonished at their story,
B042C002V019	42	2	19	while Mary treasured up all that they said, and thought about it often in her thoughts.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	And the shepherds went back, giving glory and praise to God for all that they had heard and seen, as it had been told them.  
B042C002V021	42	2	21	Eight days after the birth of the child, when it was time to circumcise him, he received the name Jesus — the name given him by the angel before his conception.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	When the period of purification of mother and child, required by the law of Moses, came to an end, his parents took the child up to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord,
B042C002V023	42	2	23	in compliance with the law of the Lord that ‘every first-born male will be dedicated to the Lord,’
B042C002V024	42	2	24	And also to offer the sacrifice required by the law of the Lord — ‘a pair of turtle-doves or two young pigeons.’
B042C002V025	42	2	25	There was at that time in Jerusalem a man named Simeon, a righteous and devout man, who lived in constant expectation of the Consolation of Israel, and under the guidance of the Holy Spirit.
B042C002V026	42	2	26	It had been revealed to him by the Holy Spirit that he should not die until he had seen the Lord’s Christ.
B042C002V027	42	2	27	Moved by the Spirit, Simeon came into the Temple Courts, and, when the parents brought in the child Jesus, to do for him what was customary under the law,
B042C002V028	42	2	28	Simeon himself took the child in his arms, and blessed God, and said:
B042C002V029	42	2	29	“Now, Lord, you will let your servant go,According to your word, in peace,
B042C002V030	42	2	30	for my eyes have seen the salvation
B042C002V031	42	2	31	Which you have prepared in the sight of all nations —
B042C002V032	42	2	32	A light to bring light to the Gentiles,And to be the glory of your people Israel.” 
B042C002V033	42	2	33	While the child’s father and mother were wondering at what was said about him,
B042C002V034	42	2	34	Simeon gave them his blessing, and said to Mary, the child’s mother: “This child is appointed to be the cause of the fall and rise of many in Israel, and to be a sign much spoken against —
B042C002V035	42	2	35	Yes, the sword will pierce your own heart — and so the thoughts in many minds will be disclosed.”  
B042C002V036	42	2	36	There was also a Prophetess named Hannah, a daughter of Phanuel and of the tribe of Asher. She was far advanced in years, having lived with her husband for seven years after marriage,
B042C002V037	42	2	37	and then a widow, until she had reached the age of eighty-four. She never left the Temple Courts, but, fasting and praying, worshiped God night and day.
B042C002V038	42	2	38	At that moment she came up, and began publicly to thank God and to speak about the child to all who were looking for the deliverance of Jerusalem.  
B042C002V039	42	2	39	When the child’s parents had done everything required by the law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee to their own town of Nazareth.
B042C002V040	42	2	40	The child grew and became strong and wise, and the blessing of God was on him.  
B042C002V041	42	2	41	Every year the child’s parents used to go to Jerusalem at the Passover Festival.
B042C002V042	42	2	42	When Jesus was twelve years old, they went according to custom to Jerusalem,
B042C002V043	42	2	43	and had finished their visit; but, when they started to return, the boy Jesus remained behind in Jerusalem, without their knowing it.
B042C002V044	42	2	44	Thinking that he was with their fellow travellers, they went one day’s journey before searching for him among their relations and acquaintances;
B042C002V045	42	2	45	and then, as they did not find him, they returned to Jerusalem, searching everywhere for him.
B042C002V046	42	2	46	It was not until the third day that they found him in the Temple Courts, sitting among the teachers, now listening to them, now asking them questions.
B042C002V047	42	2	47	All who listened to him marvelled at his intelligence and his answers.
B042C002V048	42	2	48	His parents were amazed when they saw him, and his mother said to him: “My child, why have you treated us like this? Your father and I have been searching for you in great distress.”  
B042C002V049	42	2	49	he answered.
B042C002V050	42	2	50	His parents did not understand what he meant.
B042C002V051	42	2	51	However he went down with them to Nazareth, and submitted himself to their control; and his mother treasured all that was said in her heart.
B042C002V052	42	2	52	And Jesus grew in wisdom as he grew in years, and ‘gained the blessing of God and people.’  
B042C003V001	42	3	1	In the fifteenth year of the reign of the Emperor Tiberius, when Pontius Pilate was Governor of Judea, Herod Ruler of Galilee, his brother Philip Ruler of the territory comprising Ituraea and Trachonitis, and Lysanias Ruler of Abilene,
B042C003V002	42	3	2	and when Annas and Caiaphas were high priests, a command from God came to John, the son of Zechariah, while he was in the wilderness.
B042C003V003	42	3	3	And John went through the whole district of the Jordan, proclaiming baptism on repentance, for the forgiveness of sins.
B042C003V004	42	3	4	This was in fulfilment of what is said in the writings of the prophet Isaiah —  ‘The voice of one crying aloud in the wilderness:“Make ready the way of the Lord,Make his paths straight.
B042C003V005	42	3	5	Every chasm will be filled,Every mountain and hill will be levelled,The winding ways will be straightened,The rough roads made smooth,
B042C003V006	42	3	6	and everyone will see the salvation of God.”’
B042C003V007	42	3	7	And John said to the crowds that went to be baptized by him: “You children of snakes! Who has prompted you to seek refuge from the coming judgment?
B042C003V008	42	3	8	Let your lives, then, prove your repentance; and do not begin to say among yourselves ‘Abraham is our ancestor,’ for I tell you that out of these stones God is able to raise descendants for Abraham!
B042C003V009	42	3	9	Already, indeed, the axe is lying at the root of the trees. Therefore every tree that fails to bear good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.”
B042C003V010	42	3	10	“What are we to do then?” the people asked.
B042C003V011	42	3	11	“Let anyone who has two coats,” answered John, “share with the person who has none; and anyone who has food do the same.”  
B042C003V012	42	3	12	Even tax-gatherers came to be baptized, and said to John: “Teacher, what are we to do?”  
B042C003V013	42	3	13	“Do not collect more than you have authority to demand,” John answered.
B042C003V014	42	3	14	And when some soldiers on active service asked “And we — what are we to do?” he said: “Never use violence, or exact anything by false accusation; and be content with your pay.”  
B042C003V015	42	3	15	Then, while the people were in suspense, and were all debating with themselves whether John could be the Christ,
B042C003V016	42	3	16	John, addressing them all, said: “I, indeed, baptize you with water; but there is coming one more powerful than I, and I am not fit even to unfasten his sandals. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.
B042C003V017	42	3	17	His winnowing-fan is in his hand so that he may clear his threshing-floor, and store the grain in his barn, but the chaff he will burn with a fire that cannot be put out.”  
B042C003V018	42	3	18	And so with many different appeals John told his good news to the people.
B042C003V019	42	3	19	But Prince Herod, being rebuked by John respecting Herodias, the wife of Herod’s brother, and for all the evil things that he had done,
B042C003V020	42	3	20	crowned them all by shutting John up in prison.  
B042C003V021	42	3	21	Now after the baptism of all the people, and when Jesus had been baptized and was still praying, the heavens opened,
B042C003V022	42	3	22	and the Holy Spirit came down on him in the form of a dove, and from the heavens came a voice — “You are my dearly loved son; you bring me great joy.”
