B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning the Word was;and the Word was with God;and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	He was in the beginning with God;
B043C001V003	43	1	3	through him all things came into being,and nothing came into being apart from him.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	That which came into being in him was life;and the life was the light of humanity;
B043C001V005	43	1	5	and the light shines in the darkness,and the darkness never overpowered it.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	There appeared a man sent from God, whose name was John;
B043C001V007	43	1	7	he came as a witness — to bear witness to the lightso that through him everyone might believe.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not the light,but he came to bear witness to the light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	That was the true light which enlightens everyone coming into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world;and through him the world came into being —yet the world did not know him.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came to his own —yet his own did not receive him.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	But to all who did receive him he gave power to become children of God —to those who believe in his name.
B043C001V013	43	1	13	For not to natural conception, nor to human instincts, nor to human will did they owe the new life,but to God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	And the Word became human, and lived among us,(We saw his glory — the glory of the Only Son sent from the Father),full of love and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	(John bears witness to him; he cried aloud — for it was he who spoke —“‘He who is coming’ after me is now before me,for he was ever first”);
B043C001V016	43	1	16	out of his fullness we have all received some gift,gift after gift of love;
B043C001V017	43	1	17	for the law was given through Moses,love and truth came through Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No one has ever yet seen God;God the Only Son, who is ever with the Father —He has revealed him.
B043C001V019	43	1	19	When the religious authorities in Jerusalem sent some Priests and Levites to ask John — “Who are you?”,
B043C001V020	43	1	20	he told them clearly and simply: “I am not the Christ.”
B043C001V021	43	1	21	“What then?” they asked. “Are you Elijah?” 
B043C001V022	43	1	22	“Who then are you?” they continued; “tell us so that we have an answer to give to those who have sent us. What do you say about yourself?”  
B043C001V023	43	1	23	“I,” he answered, “am —  ‘The voice of one crying aloud in the wilderness — “make a straight road for the Lord”’,  as the prophet Isaiah said.”  
B043C001V024	43	1	24	These men had been sent from the Pharisees;
B043C001V025	43	1	25	and their next question was: “Why then do you baptize, if you are not the Christ or Elijah or ‘the prophet’?”
B043C001V026	43	1	26	John’s answer was — “I baptize with water, but among you stands one whom you do not know;
B043C001V027	43	1	27	he is coming after me, yet I am not worthy even to unfasten his sandal.”
